comments.body:
For reference, with this change locally:
```
$ git diff
diff --git a/spec/models/work_spec.rb b/spec/models/work_spec.rb
index d234327..95b701d 100644
--- a/spec/models/work_spec.rb
+++ b/spec/models/work_spec.rb
@@ -337,6 +337,7 @@ RSpec.describe Work, type: :model do

   describe "datasets waiting for approval by user type" do
     before do
+      FactoryBot.create(:completed_work, created_by_user_id: user.id)
       FactoryBot.create(:draft_work, created_by_user_id: user.id)
       FactoryBot.create(:draft_work, created_by_user_id: user.id)
       FactoryBot.create(:draft_work, created_by_user_id: pppl_user.id, collection_id: Collection.plasma_laboratory.id)
```

... I see these failures:
```
  1) Work datasets waiting for approval by user type for a curator retrieves dataset created in collections they can curate
     Failure/Error: expect(described_class.unfinished_works(curator_user).length).to eq(3)

       expected: 3
            got: 4
```
```
  2) Work datasets waiting for approval by user type for a typical user retrieves only the datasets created by the user or where the user is tagged
     Failure/Error: expect(user_datasets.count).to be 3

       expected #<Integer:7> => 3
            got #<Integer:9> => 4
```
```
  3) Work datasets waiting for approval by user type for super_admins retrieves for all collections
     Failure/Error: expect(described_class.unfinished_works(super_admin_user).length).to eq(4)

       expected: 4
            got: 5
```

I don't think there's a deep bug here, but the factory name should change: `:completed_work` is intended to be complete only in terms of data entry, but it has not been approved:
```
    factory :completed_work do
      ...
      state { "awaiting_approval" }
```
but:
```
    def unfinished_works(user, search_terms = nil)
      works_by_user_state(user, ["none", "draft", "awaiting_approval"], search_terms)
    end
```
... and it'd definitely confusing for a "complete" work to be "unfinished". Adding `:approved_work` to the test instead does not cause any failures. The simple fix is to change the name of the factory to be less confusing.
